'''多語言計畫'''（Project Lingua）為一網路[[翻譯社群|翻譯社群]]，成立於2007年，希望將[[全球之聲|全球之聲]]的英文報導翻譯為其他語言，藉以建立全球[[部落客|部落客]]的溝通橋樑。該計畫目前匯集約50名[[志工|志工]]譯者與編輯，將報導翻譯為15種語言。多語言計畫、[[Cucumis_(website)|Cucumis]]等計畫，皆為全球頗具規模之網路翻譯社群。
<ref>Chris Salzberg, "[http://accurapid.com/journal/45global.htm Translation and Participatory Media: Experiences from Global Voices] {{Wayback|url=http://accurapid.com/journal/45global.htm |date=20100421090539 }}," Translation Journal, July 2008.</ref><ref>Ethan Zuckerman, "[http://www.ethanzuckerman.com/blog/2006/12/16/language-and-translation-on-global-voices/ Language and translation on Global Voices] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ethanzuckerman.com/blog/2006/12/16/language-and-translation-on-global-voices/ |date=20200724220359 }}," My heart's in Accra, December 16, 2006.</ref>

==計畫緣起==

多語言計畫構想始自於台灣部落客[[鄭國威|鄭國威]]（[[網名|網名]]Portnoy），自2005年9月起獨力將全球之聲報導翻譯為中文<ref>Paula Góes, "[http://www.globalvoices.org/2008/02/10/portnoy-zheng-the-blogger-who-inspired-the-world-to-talk-together Portnoy Zheng: The blogger who inspired the world to talk together] {{Wayback|url=http://www.globalvoices.org/2008/02/10/portnoy-zheng-the-blogger-who-inspired-the-world-to-talk-together |date=20210115171000 }}," Global Voices Online, February 10th, 2008.</ref>。這項概念於2006年全球之聲高峰會時正式命名為「多語言計畫」，此後計畫規模迅速成長。

